  "market_context": "GBP/USD on the 4-hour chart in a broader downtrend with successive swing points being swept. Price is delivering candle-by-candle through prior swing highs/lows and a fair value gap, allowing the analyst to apply the next candle model sequentially.",
  "key_observation": "When a candle sweeps a prior swing point but closes back into the range, the next candle is expected to reach the opposite extreme; respect of a PD array (fair value gap) at a sweep point sets up a next-candle continuation toward swing highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify a fair value gap below as the draw on liquidity and watch price reach for the prior low.",
    "Step 2: Observe candle closing below the previous candle and swing point, anticipating continuation lower.",
    "Step 3: Note that the next candle closes back into the range, signaling a move back above the prior high.",
    "Step 4: Track repeated sweeps of lows where candles close back inside the range, projecting reaches to the opposite highs each time.",
    "Step 5: Identify a reach down into the fair value gap which is respected, then look left to find swing highs as the next draw.",
    "Step 6: Apply the next candle model: since the fair value gap (PD array) was respected, expect price to sweep the low first then take both upside swing points.",
    "Step 7: Confirm price closes above the prior candle high and swing high, validating the bullish continuation.",
    "Step 8: Define three forward points of interest: the previous candle low, a lower fair value gap, and a deeper swing low if price closes back inside."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price respected the fair value gap, swept the low, then took out both upside swing highs as anticipated by the next candle model.",
  "lessons": "Use the next candle model fractally: a candle that sweeps a level but closes back inside projects a move to the opposite extreme. Respect of a PD array like a fair value gap is the trigger to anticipate continuation toward the next swing liquidity.",
